    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-11T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-11T03:00:00-05:00" n="128"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60d31/78: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Albright</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsingfors</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-11T10:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 11, 1934—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 11—6:34 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram No. 21, Aug. 6, 6 [<hi rend="italic">3</hi>] p.m. reached Legation
                    following call Mr. Sayre on Acting Finnish Minister for Foreign Affairs<note
                        n="22" xml:id="d128fn22">Rolf Witting.</note> and he wishes that the
                    Department know it and that he approved of Legation requesting Foreign Office
                    for decision. Acting Finnish Minister for Foreign Affairs states that experts
                    will probably be sent to Washington for exploratory conversations but that
                    official decision will not be made until the question submitted to Cabinet next
                    week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Albright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
